			<tr><td colspan="2">
				<div class="postbody">
				I was wondering...what if we would make prisons more like commies working systems.
<br />

<br />
Not the little stuff we have here and there.  Commies have a goal, which is what explain why they where succeeding to some extend.
<br />

<br />
For exemple, often we hear complain that mothers dont get enought support to raise a family.  What if, the prisonners, would be given tasks to actually help create goods and help those mothers, or some other aspect society need help.
<br />

<br />
Many prisonners have families, and often they are the most needies as well.  Even the most wretched humans can have goals, to help something they care for.
<br />

<br />
I dont say it would be a perfect system, but it could help peoples that need help and that we often have troubles to help(or cant afford to help), while somehow focusing those prisonners into ''redemption'' or whatever you wanna call it.
<br />

<br />
Of course, there would be many flaws, especially when it come to handling properly and making sure it get where it need without any selfish stealing in the process, but well, aint the idea worth a thought?
<br />

<br />
If prisonners would be given a choice of what they can help with(mothers in need would appeal to many, especially those that are fathers).  If they dont care for our roads, fine, I am sure there is something they care for and that they will give that little extra effort!
<br />

<br />
IMO, responsabilizing the prisonners and making them part of the community, no matter how twisted the form take, is the first step toward putting some sense in them, they will really feel they earn something and make the world a little better.  Especially if the prisonner feel he should never have been in jail for what he did, he can focus on something positive...
<br />

<br />
Anyway, just an idea, but humans are about choices, and if they have a choice about what they can help with, it is a start to get them a little motivated.  A prisonner can see that his childrens benefit from the stuff he work for while in jail, maybe not directly, still, they benefit from it as well as all the most needy...which is a start.
<br />

<br />
Putting them on roads building compete with a private sector that can afford those roads, while helping the poorer dont really mess the real economy...I am mostly against them working on ''quality'' products, but the basic needs that the most needy require, they should and many of them want to!
<br />

<br />
PS: Instead of having X time of salary paid completely, they could have access to the goods those made when they dont work...at least it would help with the ''maternity'' expenses companies or governements must assume, it may not be the complete solution, but it may be a start in the right direction.  You still need to manage the fees of the ''housing'' and some others aspects, but paying huge money is not a competitive solution, thereby every little step where we replace some money with goods(better value in the end then the amount they could buy possibly, could have much more food for exemple) is a step in the right direction, no?<br />
				<span class="gensmall"><br /><br />Last edited by anofalye on Mon Mar 21, 2005 3:19 am; edited 3 times in total</span><br />
				</div>
