				<div class="postbody">
				Most felons in prison are there for crimes without a victem.  Over 40% are drug crimes alone.  Not drug crimes with robbery, or drug crimes with assault, but simple possession, transportation or possession with intent to sell.
<br />

<br />
Prisons have become BIG business in our country.  We are right at the top of the world in terms of percent of population incarcerated.  In California we have 30 full sized and state run prisons, and numerous privately owned prisons and countless work camps.  Filling those prisons and the parole system is 2% of Californias Adult male population.  Looking at the number of black men only 5% of them are incarcerated here.
<br />

<br />
Prisoners are forced to work, and threatened with proxy violence if they do not take prison industry jobs workig for pennies an hour for commercial projects doled out to companies with connections.
<br />

<br />
The prison guard union here is so powerful they stop investigations dead in their tracks when guards do things like stage arena battles, or foment gang wars.  Wanna toss a prisoner into a boin cauldron of soup? Sure! go ahead!
<br />

<br />
The potential for abuse by our government to those who they take gardianship of is not only high it is critically breaking.  I would not be so concerned if people in prisons were there for real crimes but there are litterally millions of people in prison that never hurt anyone and allowing people to profit from prison labor is a sure fire formula for making sure that more and more people are classified as felons to provide that cheap workforce.<br />
				<span class="gensmall"></span><br />
